## 🚀 Getting Started

### Prerequisites

- MySQL 8.0+ (or MariaDB 10.5+)
- MySQL Workbench / DBeaver / CLI

### Setup

```bash
# 1. Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/networkdb.git
cd networkdb

# 2. Create the database and tables
mysql -u root -p < database_and_tables.sql

# 3. (Optional) Load sample data
mysql -u root -p NetworkDb < sample_data.sql

# 4. Run KPI queries
mysql -u root -p NetworkDb < kpis.sql

# 5. Run analytical queries
mysql -u root -p NetworkDb < queries.sql
```

### Quick Start — Single Query

```sql
USE NetworkDb;

-- Check network health at a glance
SELECT
    ROUND(AVG(LatencyMS), 2)                                        AS Avg_Latency_ms,
    ROUND(COUNT(CASE WHEN Status='Success' THEN 1 END) * 100.0
          / COUNT(*), 2)                                            AS Success_Rate_Pct,
    COUNT(CASE WHEN Status='Failed' THEN 1 END)                     AS Failed_Requests,
    COUNT(CASE WHEN AccessType='VPN' THEN 1 END)                    AS VPN_Sessions,
    COUNT(CASE WHEN HOUR(Timestamp) BETWEEN 0 AND 5 THEN 1 END)     AS OffHours_Access
FROM NetworkLog;
```

